12/04/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- In a letter to the BiH presidency, US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice welcomed the agreement on BiH constitutional reforms reached recently among the main BiH parties' leaders. 
Presidency chairman Sulejman Tihic said Tuesday (11 April) that Rice described the constitutional reform process as a significant step towards more functional and efficient state institutions, as well as towards BiH's integration into Euro-Atlantic structures.
In other news, the BiH Indirect Taxation Authority managing board failed to agree at its Tuesday session on the distribution of collected VAT revenues. 
Federation of BiH Finance (FBiH) Minister Dragan Vrankic blamed representatives of Republika Srpska for the failure, saying they had rejected all proposed compromises. 
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 12/04/06; Fena - 11/04/06)
